  "prompt": "What is the resolution of spy satellites?",
  "response": "The resolution of spy satellites, or reconnaissance satellites, can vary significantly depending on the technology and design specifications of the satellite. However, modern spy satellites are capable of extremely high resolution. Some of the most advanced reconnaissance satellites can achieve ground resolution of better than 30 centimeters (about 12 inches). This means they can discern objects and details on the ground that are as small as 30 centimeters across. The exact resolution capabilities are often classified information, but publicly known figures give a general idea of their capabilities.",
